<HEAD><TITLE>CTBT TALKS BOOSTED BY TWENTY-THREE NEW MEMBER COUNTRIES :</TITLE></HEAD>


<BODY BGCOLOR="000000" TEXT="FFFFFF" LINK="00FF00" VLINK="00DEFF" ALINK="00FF00">
<A HREF="index.html"><FONT SIZE=2>[Home]</FONT></A>
<CENTER>
<TABLE WIDTH=512 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD WIDTH=60></TD>
<TD WIDTH=462>

 
<H3>CTBT TALKS BOOSTED BY TWENTY-THREE NEW MEMBER COUNTRIES</H3>
 
<P><B>Greenpeace Calls for Redoubled Efforts for Successful Conclusion of CTBT Talks</B>
<P><B>GENEVA, 17th June 1996: 12 noon</B>





<P>Greenpeace applauded today's decision to admit a further twenty-three countries as full members of the Conference on Disarmament and called on the new members to bring fresh impetus to the negotiations on a comprehensive nuclear test-ban treaty (CTBT).
 

<P>'Many of these countries have long-standing and deeply held views on nuclear disarmament', said Josh Handler, Greenpeace Disarmament Campaigner. 'Their addition to the Conference on Disarmament may provide the much-needed boost
to complete a CTBT by the end of June'.
 

<P>If the CTBT is to be completed in time for signing in 1996, the treaty must be adopted by the Conference on Disarmament within the next two weeks. While the number of issues still to be resolved are few, they are also deeply divisive and go to the heart of the viability and effectiveness of the nuclear test-ban.
 

<P>These issues include whether special treatment is accorded to so-called 'Peaceful Nuclear Explosions' in the review, as insisted on by China; the regime for On-Site Inspections, and the mechanism governing the eventual entry-into-force of the
CTBT.


<P><B>The 23 new members of the Conference on Disarmament:

<P>Austria		|		Bangladesh		|	Belarus|
Cameroon	|		Chile		|		Colombia|
Finland	|		Iraq	|			Israel  |
New Zealand	|		Norway	|		Republic of Korea|
Senegal		|	Slovakia		|	South Africa  |
Spain			|	Switzerland	 |		Syria |
Turkey		|		Ukraine		|	Vietnam  |
Zimbabwe		|	Dem. People’s Rep. of  Korea  |</B>


<P><B>FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT:</B>


<P><B> Kate Johnston in Amsterdam on +31.20.523.62.16. or mobile +31.653.41.79.47 
</B>

<P><B>or</B>

<P> <B>Simon Carroll in Geneva on  +41.21.728.52.25. or mobile +41.79.213.70.67</B>

