<TD WIDTH=462>

 
<H3>Statement from Regional Representatives on board the MV Greenpeace</H3>
<P><B>On board the MV Greenpeace, off the coast of China, 12th June 1996</B>

<P>We, the representatives of neighboring NGO's of Asia and the 
Pacific are here to carry our message of peace to the Chinese 
people.  We are not here to interfere with Chinese internal affairs 
and sovereignty.  We just want to ask China to participate and 
contribute to world peace.

<P>In the same manner that we are concerned for the victims of 
radiation in Mururoa and other nuclear test sites in the world, we 
are also concerned with the impact of nuclear testing to the health 
and the environment of the indigenous people of Lop Nor.  

<P>We call on China to cancel its scheduled nuclear testing in 
September and to conclude the CTBT without conditions now.

<P>signed:

<P>Roland Oldham
<br>Tahiti "HITI TAU"

<P>Jae Hoon Choi
<br>Korean Federation for Environmental Movement

<P>Leonard Simandjuntak
<br>Indonesian Anti-Nuclear Society

<P>Murla Baldonado
<br>Nuclear Free Philippines Coalition</TD>
