<HR>
<P>SUGGESTION FOR A LETTER TO AMBASSADORS 

<br>
<P>Your Excellency,

<P>I want to protest strongly against the nuclear test China held
in Lop Nor on 8 June. This is the third time your country
has set off a nuclear test since the signing of the Non-
Proliferation Treaty in May 1995. 

<P>At the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty (NPT) conference in
May 1995, your country promised to "excercise utmost restraint" in
the field of nuclear testing.  By continuing to test
nuclear weapons, your country blatantly defies the spirit of
the Non-Proliferation Treaty, which aims to put a stop to
the spread of nuclear weapons. 

<P>It also sets back the current negotiations about the
Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty, by provoking other countries to
develop and test nuclear weapons because you do. You cannot
ask other countries to hold back on acquiring their own nuclear
arsenal unless the states which currently hold nuclear weapons
show they are prepared not to use them. Your country, as well
France, must set an example for world peace and stop
testing nuclear weapons, instead of actively continuing
the nuclear threat. 

<P>I urge you to reconsider any further plans for nuclear tests
immediately, and start working towards eliminating all nuclear
weapons by adopting a Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty now.

<P>Yours Sincerely,

<br><br><br><br>

