<HEAD>
<TITLE>Getting Involved with Greenpeace!</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FF FF FF" TEXT="#00 00 80" LINK="#00 80 00" VLINK="#80
00 00" ALINK="#FF FF 00" BASEFONT=3>
<center><a href="/~usa/index.html"><img src="pix/get_inv.gif" WIDTH=505 HEIGHT=101 border=0></a></center>
<center><table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=10>
<tr><td><IMG WIDTH=360 HEIGHT=275
SRC="pix/actnethi.gif" LOWSRC="pix/actnetlo.gif" ALT="photo of GP
action"></td><td>
<font size=+3><i>Can one person make a difference?</i>
<br><B>You bet!</B></font><br><font size=+2><i>...if that person gets involved.</i></font>
</td></tr></table></center>
<P>No one thought that seven people sailing to an island in the U.S.
nuclear test zone could  make a difference. But they did.  They created
so much opposition that one year later the island became a bird
sanctuary, instead of a nuclear test zone, and Greenpeace was born.
<P>For nearly 25 years, Greenpeace has grown into a world wide web of
people actively working  to preserve the global environment.  With the
support of concerned citizens all over the world, we  are fighting
against the over-exploitation of the marine environment, toxic waste,
destruction of  our forests, radioactive waste, global warming, and
ozone depletion.
<P>Across the country and around the world, Greenpeace draws public
attention  to environmental dangers and puts pressure on industry and
government to stop the destruction of  our planet. Whether calling
attention to these injustices through non-violent direct action, public 
education, or grassroots organizing, we need people like you to get
involved. With nearly 3 million supporters in 31 countries,
Greenpeace is creating a global movement that politicians and  corporate
leaders can't ignore.
<CENTER><H2><I>Be a part of this movement for change!</I></H2></CENTER>
<P>Support the Activist Network and be an advocate for the environment.
Work with  Greenpeace to maximize the pressure on the decision-makers
who determine the fate of entire  ecosystems. Acting together, we have
the power to protect the planet and ourselves.
<P>As a member of our Activist Network, you'll be contacted by means of 
<B>"Action Alerts"</B> that  will give you an opportunity to react to the
environment's most  urgent issues.  For example, an <B>"Action 
Alert"</B> might ask you to call your state health authorities and ask them 
<a href="pvcalert.html">take action against lead-containing PVC miniblinds</a> or
contact President Clinton to ask him to favor <a href="current.html">clean paper-making technologies</a>. 
<p>
<hr><font size=+1><b>IMPORTANT NOTE:</b>The Activist Network form on this page is intended for U.S. residents only.  
If you are not a U.S. resident, and you are interested in what you can do in 
<i>your</i> country, please check out our <a href="/greenpeace.html">International 
page</a>.</font> 
<HR><p>
