London, Moscow and Washington, <I>Entered into force</I> 5 March 1970, 729 U.N.T.S. 161, U.K.T.S. 
88 (1970), 7 ILM 809. See generally Frank Barnaby, Jozef Goldblat and Bhupendra Jasani, 
<I>Internationalization to Prevent the Spread of Nuclear Weapons</I> (London: Taylor and Francis, 1980), 
Frank Barnaby, Jozef Goldblat and Lacha Levinson, <I>The NPT: The Main Political Barrier to Nuclear 
Weapon Proliferation</I>, (London: Taylor and Francis, 1980),  William Epstein, <I>The Last Chance: 
Nuclear Proliferation and Arms Control</I> (1976), written by the United Nations Director of Disarmament 
during the negotiation of the NPT, Mohamed I.Shaker, <I>The Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty: Origin 
and Implementation</I> 1959-1979 (1980) (London and New York: Oceana Publications, 1980) and R. D. 
Burns, (ed.), 2 <I>Encyclopedia of Arms Control and Disarmament</I> (1993),  and W. Paul Gormley, 
"Book Review",  12 <I>Ga. J. Int'l  and &amp  Comp. L</I>. (1982), 459 W. Paul Gormley, "Book Review", 
14 <I>Vand. J. Transnat'l. L</I>. 687 (1981), and D. Howlett and J. H. Simpson (eds.),<I> Nuclear Non-
Proliferation Reference Handbook</I> (London: Longman, 1992), Thomas Graham, Jr., "The Duration of 
the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty Sudden Death or New Lease on Life?", 29 <I>Virginia Journal of 
International Law </I>(1989) 661-677, Adam Treiger, Adam, "Plugging the Russian brain drain: 
criminalizing  nuclear-expertise proliferation", 82 <I>Georgetown Law Journal</I> ,237-67 (November 
1993), Bill Monahan, "Giving the Non-Proliferation Treaty teeth:,  strengthening the special inspection 
procedures of the International Atomic Energy Agency", 33 <I>Virginia Journal of International Law</I> 
161-96 (Fall 1992), "Strengthening the nuclear non-proliferation,  regime: a draft convention", 26 
<I>Columbia Journal of Transnational Law</I> 167-96 (1987).

