<p><A HREF = "#textf23">  [23]<A NAME= notef23> </A> 
 
</A> For instance, some writers have concluded that there is no obstacle to the tacit renewal of a 
treaty provided that the intention of the parties to this end is clear (G. Haraszti, <I>Some Fundamental 
Problems of the Law of Treaties</I>," Akadamiai Kiado, Budapest (1973), 238-9, citing W.E. Hall, 
<I>International Law</I> (6th ed., 1909), 352.) whereas the Harvard draft Convention on the Law of 
Treaties (Harvard Draft Convention on the Law of Treaties, 1935 <I>A.J.I.L.</I> (Suppl.), 1169) preferred 
express agreement. However the express language of Article X would appear to exclude implicit renewal 
in the case of the NPT treaty.

