</A> <I>Namibia Opinion</I>, <I>supra</I> note 19, 16, 46. In that case the Court held that South 
Africa had indeed committed a material breach by repudiating the Mandate over Namibia, and recognized 
General Assembly resolution 2145 (XXI) as the exercise of the right to terminate the treaty relationship in 
case of a deliberate and persistent violation of obligations which destroys the very object and purpose of 
that relationship.

