nonbury Villas<BR>London N1 2PN<BR><P>Published by GREENPEACE INTERNATIONAL, September 1992<P><B>SUMMARY</B><P>The harmful nature of some organochlorines has been recognized for over thirty years. New scientific evidence now confirms the depth of the crisis facing the aquatic environment because of the whole group of these chemicals. Yet, despite the ever-increasing catalogue of catastrophic effects on wildlife, ranging from interference with sexual characteristics to population crashes, the release of organochlorines into the environment continues to grow.<P>This report draws on a range of scientific findings, including recent research that begins to piece together the complex mechanisms that make these chemicals so damaging, to demonstrate the urgent need for a complete phase out of all releases of organochlorines.<P><a href="56death.doc">Download the rest of this file as a Word document.(252k)</a><P><a href="56death.txt">Download the rest of this file as an ASCII document.(208k)</a></td></tr></table></center></body></HTML>
