<!--SOURCES TABLE--><a name="sources"></a><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=576><tr><tH valign=center><a href="#idc home"><img src="../icons/bpress.gif" width=576 height=72 border=0 align=center></a></td></tr>

<tr><td ALIGN=LEFT valign=top width=576><kbd>


<P><H3>Press coverage of phthalates in infant formulae 26/5/96 - 02/06/96
</H3>

<P>This list is not comprehensive, but covers most of the newspaper stories that appeared during the media "panic" over phthalates in powdered baby milk. 

<P><B>Independent on Sunday 2.6.96   ‘safety margins have been grossly eroded’</B><BR>
The baby milk alarm has shown yet again that this Government can’t handle issues of 
public health. Geoffrey Lean spells out the facts behind last weeks fudge and suggests 
how confidence could be restored...........

<P><B>Independent on Sunday 2.6.96    Ministry knew of baby milk risk for four years.</B><BR>
The Government knew four years ago that baby milk was contaminated by phthalates, 
the chemicals suspected of impairing human fertility, but decided not to publish the 
information.........

<P><B>Financial Times 1.6.96.   Baby milk producers delighted by ruling.</B><BR>
Britains baby milk manufactureers yesterday expressed delight with the European 
Commissions backing for their product - which ended a week of frenzied speculation 
over its quality.........

<P><B>The Times 1.6.96    Baby milk ‘safe’.</B><BR>
The European Commission has given British baby milk a clean bill of health.......

<P><B>The Telegraph 29.5.96    Don’t take this gall about milk.</B><BR>
We are behaving like pre-literate primitives over baby milk, says Myles Harris. 
Ministers are right to resist scare mongering and hysteria......

<P><B>Financial Times 29.5.96    Government ‘fuelled scare on baby milk’.</B><BR>
Officials deny health risks and refuse to name brands as labour accuses government of 
complacency.

<P><B>Financial Times 29.5.96    Implicated chemicals widely produced.</B><BR>
Phthalates, the chemicals at the centre of the current baby milk health scare, are 
manufactured on a large scale. World production last year was between 3m and 5m 
tonnes for use as "plasticisers". They are added to plastics, particularly PVC, to make 
them softer and more flexible......

<P><B>Independent 29.5.96   Three countries ban chemicals at centre of baby milk alert.</B><BR>
Three European countries have banned the use of the organic chemicals known as 
phthalates.........

<P><B>Independent 28.5.96   Delay over baby milk finding a ‘shambles’.</B><BR>
Attack on government insistence that there is ‘no cause for alarm’ over fertility-
threatening chemical.

<P><B>Daily Mail   28.5.96    We know best, says minister in milk scare.</B><BR>
A minister who implied that mothers maght be incapable of grasping the scientific 
background to the baby milk scare came under attack last night. ......

<P><B>Independent on Sunday 27.5.96     Sex-change chemicals in baby milk.</B><BR>
Alarming levels of chemicals that could impair human fertility have been found in 
leading brands of baby milk on sale all over Britain.......

<P><B>Daily Mail   27.5.96      Tainted baby milk storm.</B><BR>
Ministers faced angry demands last night to name nine brands of baby milk found to 
contain disturbingly high levels of chemicals which could impair fertility....... 

<P><B>Daily Mail   27.5.96       Is even baby’s milk being poisoned now?</B><BR>
Parents have few worse fears than of unwittingly feeding their babies with something 
that will stop them growing up into true men or women.........

<P><B>Daily Mirror  27.5.96    Baby milk alert. </B><BR>
Worried parents were furious yesterday as the government stayed silent over the new 
baby milk scare....... 

<P><B>Independent    27.5.96   Cover-up claim in baby milk chemicals row.</B><BR> Infertility 
threat: Mothers alarmed by test results.....   

<P><B>Independent    27.5.96    Doctors attack secrecy on baby milk chemical.</B><BR>
The refusal by the Ministry of Agriculture to name nine brands of baby milk found to 
contain chemicals linked with declining sperm levels in men drew protests from 
doctors and consumer groups yesterday.....
Tests by the Medical Research Council last year found that similar levels of phthalates 
to those in baby milks damaged the testicles and reduced sperm counts of baby rats.....

<P><B>Daily Express    27.5.96    Cover-up protest as baby milk fears grow.</B><BR>
The safety of powdered baby milk was in doubt yesterday after claims that it could 
contain chemicals which reduce fertility. 
Parents and opposition politicians accused the Government of keeping people in the 
dark over the issue.....

<P><B>The Guardian    27.5.96    ‘Cover-up’ on chemical in baby milk.</B><BR>
Mothers of bottle-fed babies were last night facing uncertainty after it emerged that 
scientists had discovered leading brands of baby milk formula contained high levels of 
chemicals that could impair human fertility. But the Government refused to disclose 
which brands.......

<P><B>The Sun    27.5.96    Baby milk scare</B><BR>
Government scientists were last night probing claims that nine brands of baby milk 
contain chemicals that reduce fertility. Consumer groups say the chemicals - known as 
phthalates - couls reduce sperm levels for babies when they grow up..... 

<P><B>The Times    27.5..96    Fertile area for confusion. </B> Contradictory evidence over the 
drop in sperm count. 
Is the quality of male sperm declining? Please don’t ask the scientists: the evidence is 
contradictory and consensus still a long way off. While some studies show a clear 
declining trend, blamed on pollution, others reveal no change or even signs of an 
increase in sperm counts.....

<P><B>The Times    27.5.96    Doctors call for names of ‘tainted’ baby milk brands.</B><BR>
Doctors and parents rounded on the Ministry of Agriculture yesterday for refusing to 
name brands of baby milk containing potentially dangerous levels of "gender-bending" 
chemicals..... 

<P><B>The Times    27.5.96    Doubts that linger over baby milk.</B><BR>
Safety levels for groups of chemicals found to have been present in 15 leading brands 
of  baby milk were drawn up before their potential effect on fertility was discovered....

<P><B>Independent on Sunday    26.5.96    Sex-change chemicals in baby milk</B><BR>
Alarming levels of chemicals that could impair human fertility have been found in 
leading brands of baby milk on sale all over Britain.....

<P><B>The People   26.5.96    Baby milk in health alarm.</B><BR>
Top brands of baby milk have been found to contain gender bender chemicals that 
could impair fertility.

