<b>Instructions for Downloading the Greenpeace Wiggling Cursor</b><p>

To download the cursor file, click on (or save by right-clicking) the following link: <a href="spermcsr.ani">Spermcsr.ani</a>.<p>
<p>

<b>Installation Instructions for Windows 95</b><p>

Click <img src="start.gif" width=56 height=26 border=0> , choose <b>"Settings"</b> and
<b>"Control Panel"</b>. You should see the Control Panel window appear as in the example
below:<p>

<img src="contrpnl.gif" width=600 height=411 border=0><p>

Double click on the <b>"Mouse"</b> icon.  The <b>"Mouse Properties"</b>
dialogue box should appear.  Click on the <b>"Pointers"</b> tab:<p>

<img src="mousprop.gif" width=404 height=448 border=0><p>

Highlight the entry called <b>"Normal Select"</b>.
Now click on the <b>"Browse"</b> button and find the Greenpeace Wriggling Cursor
file which you have downloaded.  The file is called <b>Spermcsr.ani</b>.  In the
"Mouse Properties" dialogue box, click on the <b>"Save As"</b> button.  A
<b>"Save Scheme"</b> dialogue box should appear:<p>

<img src="saveschm.gif" width=347 height=123 border=0><p>

Enter a name for the cursor scheme (for example "sperm") and click on the
<b>"OK"</b> button. In the "Mouse Properties" dialogue box, click on the
<b>"Apply"</b> button.<p>

<b>Congratulations!</b>  You have configured your Greenpeace wriggling cursor.<p>
<p><p>
<b>Un-Installing the Wriggling Cursor on Windows 95</b><p>

In the "Mouse Properties" dialogues box, under the "Pointers" tab, highlight the
"Normal Select" entry and click on the <b>"Use Default"</b> button.  Then click
on the "Apply" button.<p>
<b>Note:</b> You must enable 32 bit disk access on Windows 95 to use this feature.<p>
