<HTML><BODY TEXT="FFFF00" LINK="0000FF" VLINK="8000FF" ALINK="008040" background="../icons/xlogo.gif"><basefont=-3></font><kbd><HEAD><TITLE>Greenpeace UK science -Genetic Engineering</TITLE></HEAD><BODY><center><!--INTRO TABLE--></a><table border=0 colspan=2 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=576><tr><td valign=top align=center width=72></td><td width=504><kbd><P>


<H3>GMO Public Register</H3> 

<P>A list of Applications Received by the Secretary of State  to release genetically modified organisms to the environment.  

<P>These are some recent applications by Monsanto to release genetically manipulated organisms into the environment in the UK. The full public register is available from the Department of the Environment. 

<P><HR size=2>

<P>Reference: 96/R22/5<BR>
<P>Receipt Date: 26 February 1996
<P>Applicant:	Monsanto Plc<BR>
		Crop Protection, PO Box 53, Lane End Road, High Wycombe, 		Buckinghamshire  HP12 4HL
<P>Organism:	Sugar Beet modified with Roundup Ready genes

<P>Purpose:	Evaluation of agronomic and biological characteristics of beet crop 			transformed to be tolerant to Roundup in controlling weeds in a beet 		crop. 

<P>Release Dates: A five year programme from March 1996 to December 2000 

<P>Release Site: Auborn Farming, Auborn, Lincoln

<P>Release Areas:  75 square meters 

<P>Consent date: 27 March 1996

<P>Conditions: Yes: reporting and publication (see consent schedule)

<P><HR size=2>

